==English==

===Adverb===
'''staccato'''

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Italian ''staccato'', past participle of ''staccare'', meaning "to turn off", or "to knock off"

===Meaning===
#''Music.'' The term indicating the player to play with a sharp attack and briefly.
#A small dot under a note indicating the note is to be sounded in this musical technique.